BUTTERWORTH police are seeking public assistance with information that could help solve a murder that happened at the weekend. Police spokesperson Capt Jackson Manatha said a 23-year-old man was seen arguing with an unknown man on Saturday afternoon. Both men were seen on Scanlen Street in Butterworth. The deceased was next to his sedan car. The deceased was shot in his upper body. He was declared dead at the scene of the crime, Manatha said. The motive for the murder is not yet known. The suspect disappeared after shooting the deceased. No one has been arrested. Butterworth police are appealing to anyone who may have witnessed the murder to contact them on 047 4011100 or on Crime Stop on 0860010111. The identity of the deceased is still being withheld until his family members are informed of his murder, Manatha said. LONDEKA DLAMINI